<h2 id="red-flags">Red Flags and Scams to Avoid</h2>

<p>The extended warranty industry has more than its share of disreputable operators. Watch for these warning signs:</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Unsolicited robocalls or mailers:</strong> Legitimate warranty companies do not use scare-tactic robocalls or official-looking mailers designed to resemble government notices.</li>
<li><strong>No contract review period:</strong> Reputable providers offer a 30-60 day review period during which you can cancel for a full refund. If a company pressures you to decide immediately, walk away.</li>
<li><strong>Vague coverage descriptions:</strong> If the sales representative cannot clearly explain what is and is not covered, or refuses to provide a sample contract before purchase, that is a red flag.</li>
<li><strong>No BBB presence or poor ratings:</strong> Check the Better Business Bureau for complaints and ratings. A company with numerous unresolved complaints should be avoided.</li>
<li><strong>Extremely low prices:</strong> If a plan seems too cheap to be true, the company may have excessive exclusions or may not be financially stable enough to pay claims.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="alternatives">Alternatives to Extended Warranties</h2>

<p>If you decide an extended warranty is not right for you, consider these alternative approaches to managing repair costs:</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Self-insure with a dedicated savings account:</strong> Set aside $100-$200 per month in a dedicated vehicle repair fund. Over 3-5 years, you will accumulate $3,600-$12,000, which covers most major repairs with money left over.</li>
<li><strong>Credit union mechanical breakdown insurance:</strong> Some credit unions offer mechanical breakdown insurance (MBI) that is regulated as insurance rather than a service contract, providing stronger consumer protections at competitive prices.</li>
<li><strong>Credit card extended warranty benefits:</strong> Many premium credit cards automatically extend manufacturer warranties by 1-2 years on purchases made with the card. Check your card's benefits guide.</li>
</ul>

